          <context context-type="linenumber">10,11</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s1.p1" datatype="html">
        <source>IntuiFit (the iOS app and this website) is developed and operated by <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>Gaétan La Selve<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/>, an independent developer established in <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>France<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/>. For any question regarding this policy or your data, contact <x id="START_LINK" ctype="x-a" equiv-text="&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:codebygaetan@gmail.com&quot;&gt;"/>codebygaetan@gmail.com<x id="CLOSE_LINK" ctype="x-a" equiv-text="&lt;/a&gt;"/>.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">11,12</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s2.h" datatype="html">
        <source>Data we collect</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">18,19</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s2.p1" datatype="html">
        <source>IntuiFit records the workout data you enter in the app: workout sessions, sets, and exercises. This data is stored <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>locally on your device only<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/>, using Apple&apos;s on-device persistence framework (SwiftData), and remains there until you delete it or uninstall the app. It is never transmitted to the developer.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">19,20</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s2.p2" datatype="html">
        <source>There is <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>no account, no registration, no tracking, no analytics, and no ads<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/>. The app does not collect personal information, device identifiers, or usage statistics.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">20,21</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s2.p3" datatype="html">
        <source>Where processing falls under the GDPR, its legal basis is the <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>performance of a contract<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/> (Art. 6(1)(b)): providing the workout-tracking service you requested.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">21,23</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s3.h" datatype="html">
        <source>iCloud sync (Premium)</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">28,29</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s3.p1" datatype="html">
        <source>If you subscribe to Premium, your workout data is synced across your devices via <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>Apple CloudKit<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/>, in your private iCloud database. This data is tied to your Apple ID, encrypted by Apple, and <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>not accessible to the developer<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/> under any circumstances.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">29,30</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s3.p2" datatype="html">
        <source>Apple may store iCloud data on servers located outside the European Union, including in the United States. These transfers are governed by Apple&apos;s own safeguards, including the <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/> and standard contractual clauses. See <x id="START_LINK" ctype="x-a" equiv-text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;"/>Apple&apos;s privacy policy<x id="CLOSE_LINK" ctype="x-a" equiv-text="&lt;/a&gt;"/> for details.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">30,31</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s4.h" datatype="html">
        <source>Premium subscription &amp; payments</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">37,38</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s4.p1" datatype="html">
        <source>The Premium subscription is purchased and billed exclusively through <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>Apple&apos;s App Store<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/>. Payment is processed by Apple: the developer <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>never receives your payment details<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/> (card number, billing address, or identity). Apple only provides the developer with anonymized, aggregated transaction reports needed to operate the service.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">38,40</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s5.h" datatype="html">
        <source>Apple Health</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">45,46</context>
        </context-group>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="privacy.s5.p1" datatype="html">
        <source>If — and only if — you grant permission, IntuiFit writes workout summaries to Apple Health. The app <x id="START_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;strong&gt;"/>never reads<x id="CLOSE_TAG_STRONG" ctype="x-strong" equiv-text="&lt;/strong&gt;"/> any data from Apple Health, and Health data is never transmitted to the developer or any third party.</source>
        <context-group purpose="location">
          <context context-type="sourcefile">src/app/pages/privacy/privacy.html</context>
          <context context-type="linenumber">46,48</context>
        </context-group>
